{"word":"ἀτέλεστος","slug":"ἀτέλεστος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀτέλεστος</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:τελέω'><el>τελέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>without end</i> or <i>issue, to no purpose, without effect, unaccomplished</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>uninitiated in</i> mysteries, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}